      <!-- OVERVIEW -->
      <div class="doc-section" id="overview">
        <h2 class="docs-h2"><i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> Overview</h2>
        <p class="docs-p">
          Sneak-Up is a browser-based 2v2 tactical shooter with fog of war.
          Two teams of two spawn in opposite corners of a map and fight to eliminate each other.
          Vision is limited to line-of-sight - you can only see what your character can directly see.
        </p>
        <p class="docs-p">
          The game runs on <code>Colyseus</code> for real-time multiplayer state sync,
          <code>Express</code> for the web server, and <code>Firebase</code> for authentication.
          All game logic runs on the server; the client only renders and sends input.
        </p>
        <div class="placeholder-block">
          <p>full architecture overview coming soon</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="docs-divider">

      <!-- QUICK START -->
      <div class="doc-section" id="quickstart">
        <h2 class="docs-h2"><i class="bi bi-play-circle"></i> Quick Start</h2>
        <div class="docs-h3">1. Create an account</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          Head to <a href="/login">/login</a> and sign in with Google or create an account with email and password.
          No email verification required.
        </p>
        <div class="docs-h3">2. Choose a mode</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          From the dashboard, select <strong>Play</strong> to enter a quickplay or ranked match,
          <strong>Practice</strong> to explore a map solo, or <strong>Bot 2v2</strong> to play against AI.
        </p>
        <div class="docs-h3">3. Pick a map</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          Select from the available maps. Each has a distinct layout - open arenas, narrow corridors,
          or maze-like structures. You'll spawn in a corner with your teammate.
        </p>
        <div class="placeholder-block">
          <p>gamepad setup and control configuration docs coming soon</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="docs-divider">

      <!-- CONTROLS -->
      <div class="doc-section" id="controls">
        <h2 class="docs-h2"><i class="bi bi-keyboard"></i> Controls</h2>
        <p class="docs-p">Three control modes are available, configurable from the Options panel in the dashboard.</p>
        <div class="docs-h3">Simple Tank</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          <code>W/S</code> - move forward/back &nbsp;·&nbsp; <code>A/D</code> - rotate &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          <code>Space</code> - shoot. Direction of fire follows your heading.
        </p>
        <div class="docs-h3">Tank + Mouse</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          Move with <code>W/A/S/D</code> while aiming independently with the mouse cursor.
          <code>Left click</code> to fire.
        </p>
        <div class="docs-h3">Gamepad</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          Left stick to move, right stick to aim. <code>RT / R2</code> to shoot.
          Plug in any standard gamepad - it's detected automatically.
        </p>
        <div class="placeholder-block">
          <p>full keybinding reference and remapping docs coming soon</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="docs-divider">

      <!-- GAME MODES -->
      <div class="doc-section" id="modes">
        <h2 class="docs-h2"><i class="bi bi-grid-3x3-gap"></i> Game Modes</h2>
        <div class="docs-h3">2v2 Quickplay</div>
        <p class="docs-p">Unranked match against real players. No ELO impact. Good for learning maps and warming up.</p>
        <div class="docs-h3">Ranked 2v2</div>
        <p class="docs-p">Competitive mode with ELO tracking. Win to gain points, lose to drop. Separate from the bot ladder.</p>
        <div class="docs-h3">Bot 2v2</div>
        <p class="docs-p">
          Play with and against AI opponents. Bring your own bot brain or use the defaults.
          Useful for testing custom scripts or trained models.
        </p>
        <div class="docs-h3">Practice</div>
        <p class="docs-p">Solo offline arena. No opponents, no timer - just the map. Good for learning layouts and controls.</p>
      </div>

      <hr class="docs-divider">

      <!-- RANKED -->
